textBox.richText: Amir Dadgar-Yeganeh was born and raised in Iran until he was almost 15 years old. He then immigrated to the U.S. and started living in Los Angeles with his family.  He did his undergraduate study at UCLA and Dental school at UCSF. He was then accepted to the UCSF Orthodontic program and is currently a 3rd year orthodontic resident.
